Spatz,<br><br>
You have said your piece.  I do not want any man to reduce himself for his mistakes.  If mistakes have been made then lets pick up the pieces and move on.  Your sanity and ours are not worth any price.  We didn't start this dialogue to destroy anyone.<br><br>
Mistakes in the past should stay there.  God knows we all have things we may not be proud of.  What you are or will be starts now.  Am I disappointed?  Yes.  The man you are will be determined by your recovery from this situation.  As Cook says I will not be gullible, but I am not going to persecute you either.  Gather yourself together and post solid info and I will respond.  Your choice.<br><br>
I must admit one thing.  You sure got balls to hang on after all this.  You are free to contribute.  It will never be said that the Vet is not tolerant or fair.  You don't get any points in my book by being a super (protestor).  Just be yourself and just maybe we will all get through this.
